simpleText: I understand that comedy shows can be entertaining, and I enjoy them too. However, today's panel discussion left me disheartened. Our culture emphasizes respecting our mothers, but the abusive language used, associating the word 'mother' with private body parts, was unacceptable. While I acknowledge that times are changing, it's essential to maintain respect for our mothers on public platforms. I may face trolling for expressing this, but I implore you to reflect on the impact of such language. Let's uphold India's values of respectfully honoring our mothers and families.   #RespectOurMothers #IndianValues

simpleText: Earthing is generally used to prevent u from lightning shocks. In earthing, an electric pole is attached on your terrace and than it is connected to earth through wire. If in case lightning strikes on your house the poles absorb the light and heat waves and transfers it through wire to the ground protecting ur house from light waves. Every electric socket of the house contains earthing wire (green colored) which protects your electric appliances and your house from light waves. I hope it helps u.

simpleText: The Great Pancake Disaster  It all started on a lazy Saturday morning when I decided, for once, to try my hand at cooking something other than instant noodles and cereal. I’d seen countless cooking shows where people whipped up pancakes with such ease—flipping them in the air, smiling as if they had been born with spatulas in their hands. It was time to prove I could do it too.  I gathered the ingredients with a certain level of confidence: flour, eggs, milk, butter. It seemed simple enough. I even watched a quick tutorial online to make sure I had the basic technique down. You know, the kind where they make it look effortless, and you just feel like you're about to become a culinary genius.  Well, here's the thing—I'm not a culinary genius.  I cracked the eggs into the bowl, and it was immediately clear that I wasn’t quite sure what to do with the shell remnants that had fallen in. I stared at them for a moment, unsure whether they were a necessary part of the recipe or an accidental "bonus" ingredient. After a quick Google search, I confirmed that eggshells were, in fact, not required. With a sigh of relief, I fished them out and continued.  Next came the flour. Now, I’ve never been one for measuring. I was always that kid who thought pouring something into a cup without actually measuring it made me look more like an “artiste.” A quick glance at the flour container, a half-hearted scoop, and—voila! Flour was in the bowl. But as I stirred, I began to notice the faint, powdery mist settling over everything—my counter, my face, even my cat, who had suspiciously wandered into the kitchen, seemingly unbothered by the clouds of flour.  “Okay, this is fine,” I muttered to myself. “I’ve got this.”  And then came the milk. I poured it in, hoping for a smooth consistency. But when I looked into the bowl, what I saw looked more like a weird, lumpy mess than pancake batter. It wasn’t even remotely smooth. The flour and eggs weren’t blending, and the milk had separated into little pockets of wetness. I added more milk, just in case I’d missed something, but the batter only became more chaotic. By now, my kitchen looked like a disaster zone: flour on every surface, egg on the floor, and some mysterious sticky substance forming on the counter that could not, for the life of me, be identified.  But I pushed on. Who was I to give up now? The pancakes might not look like pancakes, but surely they’d taste like pancakes. Right?  I heated up the pan and carefully poured a spoonful of the interesting mixture into the center. It sizzled  Dhake lo chatGPT ki power. Sab chatgpt see likha he😂

simpleText: Earthing, also known as grounding, has multiple meanings, including the process of connecting electrical systems to the ground to ensure safety and the practice of connecting the body to the Earth to improve health Electrical safety Earthing is a vital part of electrical systems that protects people and equipment from electrical shock, fire, and damage. It works by providing a path for electrical current to safely flow to the ground in the event of a fault or overload. Earthing also ensures that the voltage in the system is stable and within safe limits.  Health Earthing is the practice of connecting the body to the Earth through direct skin contact, such as with bare feet or hands. Some believe that earthing can improve mental and physical health, and that it can help reduce inflammation and immune dysfunction. Earthing systems can be used at home or in the office, and can include sheets, mats, wrist or ankle bands, adhesive patches, and footwear.  Earthing systems can be constructed in a number of ways, including deep driven earth electrodes, ring earthing, and foundation earthing. The type of earthing system used depends on the requirements of the situation.

simpleText: अर्थिंग  आपको बिजली के झटके से बचाता है।जब आप किसी दोषपूर्ण विद्युत स्थापना के धातु वाले हिस्से को छूते हैं , तो उसका विद्युत प्रवाह आपके  शरीर से होकर उसके सर्किट को पूरा कर सकता है। अपने आप को एक माध्यम के रूप में सोचें जो उस उपकरण के विद्युत प्रवाह को जोड़ रहा है  धरती से जोड़ रहा है।  इसलिए जब आप किसी विद्युत उपकरण को छूते हैं और अपने शरीर से होकर एक अप्रिय धारा प्रवाहित होती हुई महसूस करते हैं ,  तो यह समय है कि आप किसी इलेक्ट्रीशियन को बुलाएँ और अर्थिंग की जाँच करवाएँ। न्यूट्रल वायर को जमीन से  जोड़कर टूटे हुए करंट पथ को पूरा करके इसे सुरक्षित किया जाता है ।
